summary.narrativeincludeclinical:
Initial report received on 07 Oct 2008 from the plaintiff's attorney in the form of a civil complaint. The attorney alleged that this consumer (plaintiff) received Zometa (zoledronic acid) (date, dosage, and indication not specified) and Actonel (risedronate). The consumer subsequently developed osteonecrosis of the jaw (date not specified). She suffered severe and permanent physical, medical injuries, and associated disabilities, pain and suffering, mental anguish, and loss of enjoyment of life. At the time of this report, the consumer's condition was unknown. No further information was provided.
Follow up received 05 May 2011 via the consumer's attorney: The patient's medication regimen and medical history were updated. In a 20 Mar 2009 progress note from the patients' oral surgeon it was reported that the patient was diagnosed with bisphosphonate related ONJ/Bisphosphonate induced osteonecrosis. It was also reported that the patient had an area of necrotic bone/1.5 cm area of exposed bone/ exposed alveolar bone, occasional sharp episodes of pain, the wound dehisced, and tooth #31 had an incomplete root canal treatment. Treatment included periodontal surgery, chlorhexidine, and penicillin-type antibiotic treatment (no other details specified).
Follow up report received on 10 Oct 2011 from the consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. The patient's demography updated. The patient's historical condition included shortness of breath. Records dated 21 Nov 2007 noted that the patient was taking Zometa 4 mg monthly from 2003 to 2006 for osteoporosis. Records dated 19 Mar 2008 noted that the patient had arthritis. The outcome of the event was not reported.
Follow up received on 11 Sep 2012 via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: The patient received Zometa for the treatment of non-small cell lung carcinoma with bone metastasis. Record dated 07 Oct 2003, noted that the patient had radiation fibrosis. Record dated 01 Dec 2003, noted that the patient had pleural effusion on the left side. Record dated 05 Jan 2004, noted that the patient had pain in the left acromioclavicular joint. Record dated 09 Mar 2004, noted that the patient had fibro thorax. Record dated 10 Mar 2004, noted that the patient had back pain. Record dated 21 May 2004, noted that the patient had light-headedness, dry mouth, pain in gums and teeth. Record dated 14 Jan 2005, noted that the patient was anemic. Record dated 07 Apr 2006, noted that the patient had abdominal discomfort. Record dated 05 Jan 2007, noted that the patient had difficulty in walking. Record dated 23 Apr 2007, noted that the patient had increasing bony pain. Record dated 10 Oct 2007, noted that the patient had posterior left lower lung thickening. Record dated 05 May 2008, noted that the patient had memory loss. Record dated 06 Jun 2008, noted that the patient had lower extremity pain. Record dated 05 Jun 2009, noted that the patient had neuropathy. Record dated 04 Jun 2010, noted that the patient was hospitalised for infected hip prosthesis. Record dated 29 Jul 2011, noted that the patient had actinic keratosis, lichenoid lymphocytic infiltrate and squamous cell carcinoma. The outcome of the events osteonecrosis of the mandible and infected hip prosthesis was stated as condition improved. The outcome of the event increasing bony pain was stated as condition deteriorated. The outcome of the other events was not reported.
Follow up received on 22 Oct 2012 via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. The patient's medical history included total left hip replacement (1986). The patient's family history included lung cancer (father, died at the age of 71). Record dated 09 Mar 2004, noted that the patient had degenerative osteoarthritis. Record dated 10 Sep 2004, noted that the patient had moderate hypertrophy, mild mitral regurgitation and mild tricuspid regurgitation. Record dated 11 Apr 2005, noted that the patient had respiratory insufficiency, chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), thromboembolic disease, esophagitis and obstructive lung disease. Record further stated that the patient underwent left lobectomy. Record dated 20 Apr 2005, noted that the patient had pulmonary embolism. Record dated 29 Jun 2005, noted that the patient had focal pleural thickening and some calcification and pulmonary consolidation in the left upper. Record dated 18 Jul 2005, noted that the patient had complete left bundle branch block, atrial premature contraction and septal dyssynchrony in the left ventricular wall asynergy. Record dated 29 Jul 2005, noted that the patient had scoliosis and mild osteoarthritis left knee. Record dated 02 May 2006 osteoarthritic changes at both shoulders. Record dated 15 Aug 2006, noted that the patient had spondylotic changes of the thoracic spine. Record further stated that the patient underwent left thoracotomy. Record dated 04 Oct 2006, noted that the patient had mild shifting of the mediastinal structures to the left and small emphysematous bullae. Record dated 31 Oct 2006, noted that the patient had asthma. The outcome of the other events was not reported.
Follow up received on 05 Nov 2012 via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: Computed tomography (CT) scan of abdomen carried out on dated 07 Oct 2003 revealed calcified granulomata in the spleen and atrophy of the left psoas muscle. Record further stated that the patient underwent CT scan of chest which revealed increase in the left sided pleural fluid accumulation. Record dated 15 Dec 2003, noted that the patient had right lobe thyroid nodule. Record dated 25 Aug 2004, noted that the patient underwent knee surgery. Record dated 21 Apr 2010, noted that the patient had nodular goiter, chronic renal failure (CRF) and hyperlipidemia. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Combined follow up received on 08 Nov 2012 and 09 Nov 2012 from physician via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. The patient's historical conditions included pneumonectomy, lump in throat, hiatal hernia, sepsis, gastroesophageal reflux with diffuse esophageal spasm, secondary malignant neoplasm of bone and bone marrow and secondary malignant neoplasm of brain and spinal cord. Record dated 21 Dec 2003 stated that patient had recurrent dislocation left total hip prosthesis. ECG performed on 22 Dec 2003 revealed right atrial enlargement. Record further stated that patient had left clavicle sclerosing deformity of the articular surface and right lung plate like atelectasis. Record dated 27 Apr 2004 stated that patient had erosive articular changes at clavicle and surrounding hypertrophy at the sternoclavicular joint. Record dated 03 May 2004 stated that patient had skin cancer excision chest. Record dated 22 Jul 2004 stated that patient had epidermal hyperplasia and parakeratosis. Record dated 18 Sep 2006 stated that patient had Bowen's disease left inferior ear. Record dated 18 May 2009 stated that patient had xerosis and skin bleeding. Record dated 07 Jul 2009 stated that patient had lymphangioma. Record dated 15 Sep 2009 stated that patient had hyperkerations of multiple 1-2 mm papules on face. Record dated 23 Jan 2012 noted hip dislocation and depression. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow up received on 26 Nov 2012 via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Record dated 22 Mar 2010 noted that patient suffered from atrial fibrillation and erosive gastritis. Record dated 30 Mar 2010 noted that patient suffered from rectal polyps. Record dated 15 Jun 2010 noted that patient was suffering from colonic diverticulosis and hemoccult positive stool. The outcome of the event was not reported.
Follow-up information received on 29 Nov 2012, via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. The medical record of 05 Jun 2012 stated the patient had pneumonia. The outcome of event was not reported.
Follow-up report received from the consumer’s attorney on 07 Dec 2012 inclusive of medical records: Patient’s medical history of lung lobectomy (1997), right total hip replacement, deep vein thrombosis prophylaxis, breast carcinoma, sciatica, fall, femur fracture and malignant neoplasm of bronchus and lung were updated. No other medical information was provided.
summary.sendercomment: Summary medical assessment: Review of available data reported in this legal case does not allow for proper causality assessments. Some conditions found in the report may not have developed under treatment with either or any of the products.
